{"schema_version": 2, "ts": "2026-05-11T12:41:26Z", "event": "clarify_critic", "feature": "vertical-planning-adoption-as-replacement-outline-absorbs-scope-boundaries-verification-strategy-risks-preserves-veto-surface-tier-conditional-acceptance", "parent_epic_loaded": true, "findings": [{"text": "The HIGH intent-clarity rating glosses over an unresolved internal contradiction: Section 1 says `## Acceptance` is for 'complex-tier only', Section 3 P10 says 'critical-tier only', and the report.py:725 touch point + Verification bullets oscillate between the two. A refining agent cannot tell which is canonical.", "origin": "primary"}, {"text": "Intent clarity rated HIGH despite the ticket bundling six concerns (1, 1a, 2, 3, 3a, 4) and admitting §3a as a documented scope expansion from #178 R5 amendment ('this ticket's scope expands to include alias-lookup...').", "origin": "primary"}, {"text": "Scope boundedness HIGH despite the Touch point conditional on ticket 174's runtime state ('if 174 lands first, edit only the lifecycle copy'). Frontmatter shows blocked-by: [] — the dependency-completion assertion is taken on faith from outside the source.", "origin": "primary"}, {"text": "Scope boundedness HIGH while accepting §3a parser hardening (metrics.py:221) as in-scope without challenge — the source explicitly narrates this as scope expansion imported from #178.", "origin": "primary"}, {"text": "Requirements alignment HIGH but the assessment doesn't engage with the source's own caveat that the rigor claim has practitioner-grade (1/5) evidence quality, which sits in tension with cortex's documented evidence-based escalation norms.", "origin": "primary"}, {"text": "Complexity rated 'complex' may be undercalibrated — the blast radius (every future plan/spec, every retro citing Veto Surface, backward-incompatible changes to in-flight artifacts) suggests criticality should be elevated.", "origin": "primary"}, {"text": "'Lands AFTER cross-skill collapse (174–176)' precondition asserted as satisfied without showing verification; frontmatter blocked-by: [] is the only machine-readable signal and it's empty.", "origin": "primary"}, {"text": "Parent epic alignment unexamined: child deletes Scope Boundaries (epic-cited) but does not touch Architectural Pattern, Open Decisions, or the implement.md §1a harness duplication the epic flags; also adds §3a metrics.py scope the epic doesn't mention. Net relationship is subset-plus-addition, not clean alignment.", "origin": "alignment"}, {"text": "Intent clarity reasoning cites a 'four-line ## What to land breakdown' that is actually six items (1, 1a, 2, 3, 3a, 4) — the rating may be HIGH but the cited evidence was miscounted.", "origin": "primary"}], "dispositions": {"apply": 2, "dismiss": 4, "ask": 3}, "applied_fixes": ["Drop the 'if 174 lands first' conditional from Touch points reasoning — verified directly that backlog/174-*.md, backlog/175-*.md, and backlog/176-*.md all have status: complete, and skills/refine/references/ now contains only clarify-critic.md. The lifecycle canonical is the sole target.", "Correct the intent-clarity citation from 'four-line breakdown' to six items (1, 1a, 2, 3, 3a, 4); the HIGH rating still holds on the merits but the cited evidence was wrong."], "dismissals": [{"finding_index": 4, "rationale": "The source ticket explicitly addresses the evidence-quality concern via the mandated provenance note ('community-derived from CRISPY/QRSPI... empirical case... is practitioner-grade — adopt because it helps human review and forces explicit phase thinking, not because the research literature mandates it') and the language constraint ('Don't quote the unverified more reliable than any prompt instruction superlative as fact in cortex docs'). CLAUDE.md's MUST-escalation policy governs MUST-language behavior escalations, not template-pattern adoption — no policy conflict."}, {"finding_index": 5, "rationale": "Cortex's complexity dimension is binary (simple|complex) per clarify.md §3 — 'complex' is the top of the scale, not undercalibrated. Criticality is the orthogonal dimension; rated HIGH (not CRITICAL) because the change is recoverable (templates can be reverted) and does not match the critical rubric ('security, data loss, financial, OR loss of a core capability everything else depends on'). Template restructuring restructures HOW plans are authored, it does not lose a core capability."}, {"finding_index": 6, "rationale": "Dependencies were verified by direct inspection: `grep -E 'status:' backlog/{174,175,176}-*.md` returned `status: complete` for all three. The frontmatter blocked-by:[] is correct for the current state — there is nothing blocking 182 now. The conditional Touch point has resolved cleanly: refine/references/specify.md no longer exists, so only the lifecycle canonical is in scope."}, {"finding_index": 7, "rationale": "Parent epic alignment is properly governed by research/vertical-planning/decomposed.md, which explicitly assigns 182 the 'outline + phases + gates + parser test' scope as Stream F. Other epic findings (Architectural Pattern, Open Decisions, implement.md §1a, refine/SKILL.md copy-paste bug) are explicitly assigned to sibling tickets 173/177/180. The §3a addition is documented via the #178 R5 amendment trail. Net relationship is correctly subset-plus-amendment within the established decomposition."}], "status": "ok"}
